               <msContents>
                  <summary>A major work on religious obligations and moral duties, extracted from the author's Arabic work <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Iḥyā’ ‘Ulūm al-Dīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar">احياء علوم الدين</title>
                     <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f1155">Ghazzālī, 1058-1111</persName> was considered to be the greatest authority on Shafi‘ī branch of Islamic law, and was entitled Hujjat al-Islam. He wrote about one hundred books and treatises, mostly in Arabic, but also a few in Persian, including the present work, which is a Persian abridgement of his Arabic work, <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Iḥyā ‘Ulūm al-Dīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar">احيا علوم الدين</title>, divided into four rukn. Volume one, in 93 folios and 2 fly leaves, contain a general brief preface <locus from="1v" to="1v">ff.lv-3v</locus>, an introduction on cognition, divided into four ‘unvān from <locus from="3v" to="3v">3v</locus> to <locus from="43r" to="43r">43r</locus> and the first rukn entitled ‘bādāt, divided into ten aṣl from <locus from="43r" to="43r">f. 43r</locus> to <locus from="93r" to="93r">f. 93r</locus>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_231-item1">
                     <author key="person_89736851" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/89736851/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ghazzālī, 1058-1111</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">الغزالي</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_3797">Kīmiyā-yi saʻādat</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_3797">كيمياى سعادت</title>
                     <note>Volume I of IV. Unanimously written by the same hand.</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="beginning">شکر و سپاس فراوان بعدد ستارگان آسمان و قطره باران و برگ درختان و ریگ بیابان و ذره های زمین و آسمان مران خدایرا</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">اصل اول در اعتقاد اهل سنت است بدانکه هر که مسلمان شود اول واجب بر وی انست که کلمه های لا اله الا الله محمد رسول الله را که زبان گفت بدل بداند و باور کند</explicit>
                     <listBibl>
